@startuml
title Use Case 6: Group Chat Functionality

actor User
boundary GUI as "Client GUI"
control Client as "Client App"
control Server as "Server"
collections ClientCache as "Client Cache\n(User directory + Conversation headers)"
collections Cache as "Server Cache\n(Users + Conversation headers)"
collections Store as "Server Persistent Storage\n(Conversation headers)"

== Create group conversation ==
User -> GUI: Choose "Create Group Conversation"
GUI -> Client: Request user directory
Client -> Server: GetAllUsers()
Server --> Client: User list
Client -> ClientCache: Cache user list
Client --> GUI: Provide user list for display

User -> GUI: Select participants\nEnter group name\nClick "Create"
GUI -> Client: CreateGroupConversation(name,\n participantUserIds)

Client -> Server: CreateConversation(type=group,\n name, participants)
Server -> Store: Create conversation header\n(conversationId, name, participants)
Store --> Server: Created (conversationId, header)
Server -> Cache: Update conversation headers
Server --> Client: CreateConversation OK\n(conversationId, header)

Client -> ClientCache: Add conversation header
Client -> GUI: Open group conversation view

== Add users later ==
loop When user adds participants
  User -> GUI: Choose "Add Members"
  GUI -> Client: Request user directory (if needed)
  Client -> Server: GetAllUsers()
  Server --> Client: User list
  Client -> ClientCache: Cache/refresh user list
  Client --> GUI: Provide user list

  User -> GUI: Select users to add\nClick "Add"
  GUI -> Client: AddParticipants(conversationId,\n userIdsToAdd)
  Client -> Server: AddParticipants(conversationId,\n userIdsToAdd)

  Server -> Store: Update participants list\n(add users)
  Store --> Server: Updated header
  Server -> Cache: Update conversation headers

  Server --> Client: AddParticipants OK\n(updated header)

  == Notify logged-in participants ==
  loop For each logged-in participant client
    Server --> Client: PushConversationUpdate\n(conversationId, updated header)
    Client -> ClientCache: Update cached header
    Client -> GUI: Update participants UI
  end
end

== Leave group conversation ==
User -> GUI: Choose "Leave Group"
GUI -> Client: LeaveConversation(conversationId)
Client -> Server: RemoveParticipant(conversationId,\n userId=self)

Server -> Store: Update participants list\n(remove user)
Store --> Server: Updated header
Server -> Cache: Update conversation headers
Server --> Client: LeaveConversation OK\n(updated header)

== Notify remaining logged-in participants ==
loop For each remaining logged-in participant client
  Server --> Client: PushConversationUpdate\n(conversationId, updated header)
  Client -> ClientCache: Update cached header
  Client -> GUI: Update participants UI
end

Client -> ClientCache: Remove/mark conversation\nas left for this user
Client -> GUI: Close conversation view\nReturn to conversation list
@enduml
